<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_CDS"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_CDS"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange Credit Default Swaps (CDSs).</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Credit Default Swaps</title>

    <para role="TEXT">A Single Name Credit Default Swap (CDS) contract is an insurance
    contract covering the risk that a specified credit defaults. Following a
    defined credit event, the protection buyer receives a payment from the
    protection seller to compensate for credit losses. In return, the
    protection buyer pays a premium to the protection seller over the life of
    the contract.</para>
  </section>

